<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>be on the fiddle • fiddle about</xh5><p> <i>be on the fiddle</i>—(sl.) be involved in illicit money-making activities: As it was day-time, everyone in the coffee bar was on the dole or <u>on the fiddle</u>.</p><p><i>fiddle about</i>—(coll.) mess about or waste time: I’ve been <u>fiddling about</u> for ages trying to get the windscreen washers to work properly.</p> </entry>
